  <info>
    <link type="guide" xref="mongoc_client_t" group="function"/>
  </info>
  <title>mongoc_client_set_appname()</title>

  <section id="synopsis">
    <title>Synopsis</title>
    <synopsis><code mime="text/x-csrc"><![CDATA[bool
mongoc_client_set_appname (mongoc_client_t *client,
                           const char      *appname)
]]></code></synopsis>
    <p>Sets the "appname" metadata for the client. This string, along with the metadata set in <code xref="mongoc_metadata_append">mongoc_metadata_append</code> is sent to the server as part of the initial connection handshake (<link href="https://docs.mongodb.org/manual/reference/command/isMaster/">"isMaster"</link>)</p>
    <p>If <code>appname</code> is longer than <code>MONGOC_METADATA_APPNAME_MAX</code>, this client has already sent an "isMaster" command, or this client is from a <code xref="mongoc_client_pool_t">mongoc_client_pool_t</code>, then this function will do nothing and return false. If it successfully sets the appname, it will return true.</p>
    <p><code>appname</code> is copied, and doesn't have to remain valid after the call to <code>mongoc_client_set_appname()</code>.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="parameters">
    <title>Parameters</title>
    <table>
      <tr><td><p>client</p></td><td><p>A <code xref="mongoc_client_t">mongoc_client_t</code>.</p></td></tr>
      <tr><td><p>appname</p></td><td><p>The application name, of length at most <code>MONGOC_METADATA_APPNAME_MAX</code>.</p></td></tr>
    </table>
  </section>
</page>
